data.description: **Price Improvement***This stunning 4 bed 3 bath POOL home in Pepper Tree Village hosts over 2,060 sqft of meticulously maintained living space with countless upgrades. This gorgeous block and stucco home is dressed with stone veneer, warm tones, and the current owners have elevated the curb appeal even further with the addition of professional landscaping and rain gutters. The inside of this home is bright and spacious with an open floor plan. Wood-look tile flows beautifully throughout the living areas connecting the Living Room, dining room and kitchen. High ceilings give an added sense of spaciousness and the pocket glass sliding doors leading to the pool area allow an abundance of natural light to fill the home and disappear into the wall to create the ultimate entertaining space. The kitchen is a home-chefs dream come true complete with stone counters, an island, a GAS range, range hood, stainless steel appliances, modern tile backsplash, coffee nook, built-in pantry, and ample counter AND cabinet space. The master bedroom had a beautiful view and private entrance to the pool area. The ensuite master bathroom has a generously sized tiled walk-in shower, a soaking tub, dual vanities, and a closet big enough for the entire family! On the other side of the home are 2 of the additional 3 bedrooms, along with 2 more FULL bathrooms- one finished with dual vanities and a walk-in tiled shower, the other is a cabana bath finished with a tiled tub/shower combo and a separate entrance to the pool area. The 4th bedroom is located at the front of the house (currently being utilized as an office) boasting French doors, a closet, and views of the front yard. But the real show stopper of this home is the pool area! Completely covered by an expansive screen enclosure, this enormous entertaining space is sure to keep your friends and family visiting all year long. There is a covered section for shade with outlets for a TV, and plenty of pool decking providing many spaces to lounge, play, and create memories. The pool is heated and complete with a water feature and there is still ample yard space for pets or gardening. Located in Wildwood just minutes from the Villages, this neighborhood provides you with a small-town feel while still being just a short drive away from schools, medical facilities, shopping, entertainment, professional plazas and employment/professional opportunity. Quick access to 75 and the Florida Turnpike make day trips and traveling easy. Schedule a showing or call today to see how we can make this stunning house your new home!
